I'm at the market.

13
00:02:39,479 --> 00:02:41,000
I found two good lamb vendors.

14
00:02:41,599 --> 00:02:42,280
Let's try them first.

15
00:02:42,599 --> 00:02:43,599
The two bags are different.

16
00:02:43,599 --> 00:02:44,960
Tell me which one tastes better.

17
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:45,680
We should

18
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:47,280
cook two dishes and taste them first.

19
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:48,479
Serve them only if they're good.

20
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:49,319
No problem.

21
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:51,039
Ming Liang

22
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:51,960
Ming Liang

23
00:02:52,199 --> 00:02:52,560
Sister Buli

24
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:54,360
Someone at the corner is arguing

25
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:55,520
because of your restaurant.

26
00:02:58,280 --> 00:02:59,719
Have you been to Hong Shiliu Restaurant?

27
00:02:59,719 --> 00:03:01,039
You say it's just for show.

28
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:03,599
That seat is for those in need.

29
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:05,639
This is clearly just a marketing stunt.

30
00:03:05,639 --> 00:03:06,719
You're just a shill, aren't you?

31
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:08,280
How am I a shill?

32
00:03:08,639 --> 00:03:09,400
Let go of me.

33
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:10,599
Let me explain to you.

34
00:03:10,680 --> 00:03:12,319
Hong Shiliu Restaurant has been open for thirty years.

35
00:03:12,319 --> 00:03:13,159
I'm calling the police!

36
00:03:13,159 --> 00:03:14,439
A lot of people know about this seat.

37
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:15,000
Go ahead and ask.

38
00:03:15,039 --> 00:03:15,680
A fake can't pass for real.

39
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:16,639
And the real can't be faked.

40
00:03:16,639 --> 00:03:17,360
Let's talk this out calmly.

41
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:18,520
I know, I know, fine.

42
00:03:18,599 --> 00:03:19,439
Let go.

43
00:03:19,439 --> 00:03:20,159
So annoying.

44
00:03:21,439 --> 00:03:22,319
You're Ming Liang.

45
00:03:24,639 --> 00:03:25,080
Yes.

46
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:27,439
I finally get to meet you, Ming Liang.

47
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:30,719
You look way better in person than in photos.

48
00:03:32,080 --> 00:03:33,159
You, you are...

49
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:34,639
Mom

50
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:36,800
Someone's here for you.

51
00:03:45,719 --> 00:03:46,599
Mama Aiyixia

52
00:03:46,879 --> 00:03:47,639
Mayila

53
00:03:48,719 --> 00:03:49,840
Mayila, I missed you so much!

54
00:03:51,719 --> 00:03:52,960
I missed you too!

55
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:55,520
I...

56
00:03:56,159 --> 00:03:56,960
When I was in school,

57
00:03:56,960 --> 00:03:59,240
it was Mama Aiyixia who secretly supported me.

58
00:03:59,719 --> 00:04:00,240
You didn't know, did you?

59
00:04:04,879 --> 00:04:06,759
You made my kindness

60
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:08,639
blossom even more.

61
00:04:10,479 --> 00:04:11,280
After graduation,

62
00:04:11,280 --> 00:04:13,879
I thought she'd stay in Urumqi.

63
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:16,079
But she insisted on going back to Fuyun.

64
00:04:16,439 --> 00:04:18,639
She became a childcare counselor.

65
00:04:18,639 --> 00:04:19,000
That's right.

66
00:04:21,399 --> 00:04:21,800
At that time,

67
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:23,560
weren't you working and studying elsewhere?

68
00:04:24,240 --> 00:04:25,560
Every time I came back to Hong Shiliu,

69
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:27,240
we always just missed each other.

70
00:04:27,839 --> 00:04:29,439
This time I came to Urumqi

71
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:30,839
to buy a projector for the kids.

72
00:04:30,920 --> 00:04:33,040
I was determined to visit Hong Shiliu.

73
00:04:33,319 --> 00:04:33,759
See?

74
00:04:33,839 --> 00:04:34,759
Good thing I came back.

75
00:04:35,399 --> 00:04:36,759
Now we siblings finally get to meet.

76
00:04:36,839 --> 00:04:37,240
Right?

77
00:04:38,639 --> 00:04:39,040
No.

78
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:40,000
Wait a second.

79
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:44,120
Wasn't my mom an anonymous sponsor?

80
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:45,639
How did you know

81
00:04:45,639 --> 00:04:47,240
it was my mom who helped you?

82
00:04:50,959 --> 00:04:53,040
When I was studying in Urumqi,

83
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:54,639
whenever I had time,

84
00:04:54,959 --> 00:04:56,480
I went out looking for my sponsor.

85
00:04:57,240 --> 00:04:58,079
I wanted

86
00:04:58,199 --> 00:05:00,600
to thank her in person.

87
00:05:01,399 --> 00:05:03,240
From bits and pieces in her letters,

88
00:05:03,759 --> 00:05:06,360
I learned she ran a restaurant in Urumqi.

89
00:05:07,519 --> 00:05:09,199
There are so many restaurants in Urumqi.

90
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:11,639
I went to each one,

91
00:05:12,079 --> 00:05:13,560
asking at every place.

92
00:05:14,199 --> 00:05:15,399
Until that day...

93
00:05:29,319 --> 00:05:30,959
If you're going through hard times,

94
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:32,639
just pause for a moment.

95
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:38,079
If you're facing difficulties,

96
00:05:38,079 --> 00:05:39,319
please take a break.

97
00:05:47,199 --> 00:05:47,959
Miss

98
00:05:50,199 --> 00:05:50,879
Miss

99
00:05:54,079 --> 00:05:55,160
One order of pilaf, please.

100
00:05:58,519 --> 00:05:59,199
Hello.

101
00:06:04,399 --> 00:06:05,399
I'm Mayila.

102
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,160
Now that the restaurant is so popular,

103
00:06:09,959 --> 00:06:11,160
you still keep that seat.

104
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:13,600
You're the kindest person

105
00:06:13,759 --> 00:06:15,240
I've ever met, truly the kindest.

106
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:17,800
It's no big deal.

107
00:06:18,360 --> 00:06:19,120
People

108
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:20,399
should always

109
00:06:20,920 --> 00:06:22,000
remember their roots.

110
00:06:22,839 --> 00:06:24,040
Whether I'm here or not,

111
00:06:24,959 --> 00:06:27,800
that table must always be there.

112
00:06:29,319 --> 00:06:30,759
You'll always be here.

113
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:32,040
You're so good,

114
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:32,920
so kind.

115
00:06:33,240 --> 00:06:34,079
Good things happen to good people.

116
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:35,199
You'll live a long, happy life.

117
00:06:35,759 --> 00:06:37,439
Hong Shiliu Restaurant will only get more popular.

118
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:38,560
Right?

119
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:41,759
This girl...

120
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:42,560
Let's eat.

121
00:06:49,199 --> 00:06:49,839
Brother Ming Liang

122
00:06:49,959 --> 00:06:50,759
Your needs,

123
00:06:50,759 --> 00:06:52,000
our boss already told me about them.

124
00:06:52,199 --> 00:06:53,279
This projector here

125
00:06:53,279 --> 00:06:54,360
is a great fit.

126
00:06:54,439 --> 00:06:55,480
It has higher lumens,

127
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:55,959
so it's brighter.

128
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:57,199
For example, in a classroom during the day,

129
00:06:57,199 --> 00:06:58,920
you can see clearly even without curtains.

130
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:00,759
Many schools in our city

131
00:07:00,759 --> 00:07:01,639
use this exact model.

132
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:03,160
Your recommendation is definitely solid.

133
00:07:05,519 --> 00:07:06,920
What are they buying lately?

134
00:07:07,399 --> 00:07:07,879
Recently,

135
00:07:07,879 --> 00:07:09,000
drones have been selling well.

136
00:07:09,079 --> 00:07:09,879
A lot of herders

137
00:07:09,879 --> 00:07:10,480
come to buy them.

138
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:12,439
Herders buying drones?

139
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:13,639
To shoot short videos?

140
00:07:13,759 --> 00:07:14,560
Of course not.

141
00:07:14,639 --> 00:07:15,439
They use them for herding sheep.

142
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:16,279
Herding sheep?

143
00:07:16,439 --> 00:07:16,759
Here,

144
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:17,879
let me show you.

145
00:07:18,319 --> 00:07:18,759
Look here.

146
00:07:19,160 --> 00:07:19,560
This one

147
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:21,879
was tested by herders on the Bayanbulak Grassland.

148
00:07:21,879 --> 00:07:23,759
It has smart tracking and thermal imaging.

149
00:07:24,079 --> 00:07:25,680
It can automatically count the flock.

150
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:27,199
If a sheep goes missing,

151
00:07:27,199 --> 00:07:28,839
it instantly detects and alerts you.

152
00:07:28,879 --> 00:07:30,040
It's even faster than riding a horse.

153
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:31,759
Really?

154
00:07:32,040 --> 00:07:32,560
Let me see.

155
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:34,399
You want to buy one too?

156
00:07:34,399 --> 00:07:34,879
No,

157
00:07:35,439 --> 00:07:36,240
I have a friend

158
00:07:36,319 --> 00:07:37,600
who does wildlife rescue.

159
00:07:37,639 --> 00:07:38,560
I wonder if she could use it.

160
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:39,560
And this one,

161
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:40,319
this here

162
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:41,600
is a solar-powered collar.

163
00:07:41,759 --> 00:07:42,439
Put this

164
00:07:42,439 --> 00:07:43,160
on the sheep.

165
00:07:43,199 --> 00:07:44,680
If a sheep lies down

166
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:45,199
or wanders off,

167
00:07:45,199 --> 00:07:46,319
the phone app

168
00:07:46,319 --> 00:07:47,879
will detect and alert you automatically.

169
00:07:47,920 --> 00:07:49,639
It's even sharper than an old herder's eyes.

170
00:07:50,319 --> 00:07:50,879
Let me see.

171
00:07:51,519 --> 00:07:53,800
Back then, if we didn't do well in school,

172
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:54,959
our parents would say,

173
00:07:55,319 --> 00:07:56,560
"If you don't study, you'll herd sheep."

174
00:07:56,959 --> 00:07:57,959
Now, if you don't study,

175
00:07:57,959 --> 00:07:59,199
you can't even herd sheep right.

176
00:08:01,079 --> 00:08:03,000
Is this expensive?

177
00:08:05,319 --> 00:08:06,879
This childcare instructor job of yours,

178
00:08:06,879 --> 00:08:07,920
what exactly do you do?

179
00:08:08,360 --> 00:08:10,639
Simply put, it's like being a child educator.

180
00:08:11,079 --> 00:08:12,639
Mainly for our herding areas,

181
00:08:12,639 --> 00:08:13,680
for children aged zero to three,

182
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:15,360
providing early education.

183
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:17,000
That's it.

184
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:19,639
So, you must have a lot of cattle and sheep.

185
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:20,319
Buying this?

186
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:21,759
No,

187
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:23,519
we don't have that many.

188
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:24,480
I...

189
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:26,680
I'm buying it for a friend.

190
00:08:27,519 --> 00:08:29,199
He's kind of

191
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:32,000
the leader in our area.

192
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:34,159
His family has a lot of livestock.

193
00:08:34,559 --> 00:08:36,440
I figured he could use it.

194
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:38,960
You're buying this gear out of your own pocket—

195
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:40,840
not just a good teacher,

196
00:08:40,879 --> 00:08:42,120
but a great friend too.

197
00:08:43,039 --> 00:08:44,759
Isn't this what Mama Aiyixia taught me?

198
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:46,080
You know,

199
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:47,320
when I just graduated,

200
00:08:47,639 --> 00:08:48,519
I actually had a chance

201
00:08:48,519 --> 00:08:49,759
to stay in Urumqi.

202
00:08:50,879 --> 00:08:53,000
But there was always a voice

203
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,759
calling me back to the grasslands.

204
00:08:55,720 --> 00:08:56,840
I come from the herding area,

205
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:57,679
so I know

206
00:08:57,879 --> 00:09:00,000
kids there can only change their fate

207
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:01,000
by studying.

208
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:02,879
My grandpa was really upset then.

209
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:04,200
He didn't want me to go back.

210
00:09:04,519 --> 00:09:06,000
He was just worried about you.

211
00:09:06,440 --> 00:09:07,440
Yeah, I know.

212
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:10,120
But I didn't know how to convince him.

213
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:11,679
So I went to Mama Aiyixia.

214
00:09:12,080 --> 00:09:14,000
She actually wanted me to stay too.

215
00:09:14,399 --> 00:09:16,679
But after she knew I wanted to go back,

216
00:09:16,679 --> 00:09:19,679
she made a special trip to Fuyun.

217
00:09:19,879 --> 00:09:21,080
She talked to my grandpa.

218
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:22,240
In the end, he agreed.

219
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:23,440
So this time,

220
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:24,440
I'm thinking

221
00:09:24,679 --> 00:09:26,440
of taking Mama Aiyixia to Fuyun for a few days.

222
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:29,120
My grandpa always misses her.

223
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:32,799
Alright.

224
00:09:32,879 --> 00:09:33,679
You tell her.

225
00:09:33,679 --> 00:09:34,879
See what she says.

226
00:09:35,679 --> 00:09:36,399
But...

227
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:38,000
But what?

228
00:09:38,879 --> 00:09:39,240
It's nothing.

229
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:40,200
Just talk to her.

230
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:42,120
What do you mean, nothing? What's up?

231
00:09:42,399 --> 00:09:43,200
Nothing, really.

232
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:44,799
Ming Liang,

233
00:09:46,679 --> 00:09:48,879
I saw you earlier in that restaurant,

234
00:09:48,879 --> 00:09:49,759
running around,

235
00:09:49,759 --> 00:09:50,879
managing things.

236
00:09:51,639 --> 00:09:52,799
It felt off to me.

237
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:54,200
Didn't Mama Aiyixia say

238
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:55,320
you were going to be a painter?

239
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:56,879
Wasn't that your dream?

240
00:09:56,919 --> 00:09:58,440
She's someone who supports her child's dreams.

241
00:09:58,440 --> 00:10:00,440
How could she let you give up painting

242
00:10:00,879 --> 00:10:02,679
to run a restaurant instead?

243
00:10:02,879 --> 00:10:04,240
Is something going on with you two?

244
00:10:04,679 --> 00:10:05,799
At the restaurant,

245
00:10:07,639 --> 00:10:08,360
I just don't want

246
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:09,679
her to work too hard alone.

247
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:10,960
Ming Liang,

248
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:12,840
in my heart,

249
00:10:12,840 --> 00:10:14,440
Mama Aiyixia is like my own mother.

250
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:15,320
She's the same to me.

251
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:17,320
So to me,

252
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:18,559
you're like family too.

253
00:10:18,559 --> 00:10:20,080
Like my own little brother.

254
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:21,759
If anything's wrong,

255
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,200
don't keep it from me.

256
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:23,879
Okay?

257
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:26,360
If there's anything I can help with,

258
00:10:28,879 --> 00:10:30,440
please treat me as family too.

259
00:10:30,440 --> 00:10:30,960
Alright?

260
00:10:35,519 --> 00:10:36,279
Mom...

261
00:10:41,159 --> 00:10:42,320
Mom has a brain tumor.

262
00:10:47,279 --> 00:10:49,440
A... a brain tumor?

263
00:10:58,799 --> 00:11:00,399
I took all my annual leave this time

264
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:01,679
to spend more days with you.

265
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:02,720
Okay.

266
00:11:03,679 --> 00:11:04,720
So many new stores opened.

267
00:11:05,360 --> 00:11:06,080
Yeah.

268
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:08,720
We're here, we're here.

269
00:11:09,279 --> 00:11:09,679
Thank you.

270
00:11:10,759 --> 00:11:11,279
Right here.

271
00:11:20,720 --> 00:11:21,279
Alright.

272
00:11:21,759 --> 00:11:24,559
You’re such an honest kid.

273
00:11:24,799 --> 00:11:26,159
Every time you visit me,

274
00:11:26,519 --> 00:11:28,080
you always bring me here for photos.

275
00:11:28,879 --> 00:11:29,840
I just thought

276
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:31,759
we could grow old together.

277
00:11:35,399 --> 00:11:36,120
What’s wrong?

278
00:11:37,759 --> 00:11:38,279
Nothing.

279
00:11:39,679 --> 00:11:41,159
You can’t lie, can you?

280
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:43,159
Is it about your feelings?

281
00:11:43,559 --> 00:11:45,039
You saw right through me.

282
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:47,720
How are things with your crush?

283
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:49,440
It’s just the same.

284
00:11:49,960 --> 00:11:50,799
I like him.

285
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:52,919
He doesn’t like me.

286
00:11:54,559 --> 00:11:56,200
It’s fine, don’t worry about me.

287
00:11:56,960 --> 00:11:58,279
Persistence pays off.

288
00:11:58,440 --> 00:11:59,320
So one day,

289
00:11:59,679 --> 00:12:01,080
I’ll melt his heart for sure.

290
00:12:01,399 --> 00:12:02,559
It’s just a matter of time.

